<paragraph blockId="71.[701,1228,1647,1759]" lastBlockId="72.[93,619,1259,1759]" lastPageId="72" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="71" pageNumber="71">Head with length and width equal to or about a fifth wider than long (HW/HL: 1.0–1.2). Frontoclypeal ridge complete, not separated medially. Dorsal surface without V-shaped depression; surface polished and coarsely punctate; punctation dense, less dense basally and laterally. Labrum quadridentate; surface without tubercle near submedial denticle.</paragraph>
